      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry, fluid, and operating conditions must be sufficiently similar to the COU device and conditions to support extrapolation of validation evidence.",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which is the same device class and flow regime as the CPB pump assessed in this COU. Blood analog fluid (glycerin-water mixture with matched viscosity) was used in experiments. Operating conditions span the clinical CPB envelope. Geometric similarity index > 0.92 relative to the production device."
    },
    {
